The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                 NATION BRIEFS
                              
	 New Delhi, Jan. 28 (PTI): A Japanese diplomat lost his belongings while watching Republic Day celebrations in a heavily-guarded VIP enclosure at Rajpath, raising questions over security arrangements.           An FIR has been lodged at Tughlak Road police station and officers are checking CCTV footages to find the culprit.                  
	 Mangalore (PTI): Mangalore police have sought the custody of Ram Sena president Pramod Mutalik, who has defended the outfits attack on a pub last week, a police official said. The police have requested the Davangere court to hand over Mutalik for interrogation, IGP A.M. Prasad said.                   
	 New Delhi (PTI): Performing yoga is not un-Islamic as offering namaz is also a form of the practice, leading seminary Darul Uloom has said, rubbishing the controversy over the issue.
                                                                                                                           
